                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sorsby</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">La Paz, Bolivia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 230.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 226 of February 22 last,
                    relative to Perú’s previous unfavorable attitude toward the execution of the <pb
                        facs="0214" n="108" xml:id="pg_108"/> parcels-post treaty between Bolivia
                    and the United States, I now have the honor to report that I am informed by the
                    Bolivian minister of foreign affairs that Perú has finally consented to
                    facilitate the transit of all postal parcels between the United States and
                    Bolivia and that instructions to that effect have been given to the respective
                    subordinate authorities.</p>
                <p>I have the honor, etc., etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William B. Sorsby.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
